# Clifford.Even

Even subalgebra of a Clifford algebra and its spinorial structure.

The even subalgebra Cl⁺(V, Q) consists of elements built from even products of vectors.
For Cl(ℝ⁴, η₃₊₁), the even subalgebra is isomorphic to ℍ ⊕ ℍ (Dirac spinors split).

Mathlib provides this via `CliffordAlgebra.even`.

Source: Lawson–Michelsohn, "Spin Geometry", Chapter I.
Convention: follows `PhysicsSM.Clifford.Basic` signature conventions.

Prerequisites:
- `PhysicsSM.Clifford.Basic`

Status: stub — even subalgebra structure and spinor decomposition to be added.
